bug.short_desc: qx.ui.table error when pressing page down key in Internet Explorer

long_desc.thetext:
When eg. in demo/text/Table_1.html displayed by Internet Explorer the page down key is pressed the following error is displayed:
008704: Could not dispatch event of type "keydown": TypeError - 'this._getColToXPosMap()[...].visX' ist Null oder kein Objekt (#-2146823281) 010266: Could not dispatch event of type "keydown": TypeError - 'this._getColToXPosMap()[...].visX' ist Null oder kein Objekt (#-2146823281)
Despite of this error the table correctly srolls one page down. The bug is only displayed the first time after the table is fresh displayed.
A screen snapshot is attached which shows the bug.
No, nothing new. I'm currently working on another project. Any contributions are welcome.

this._focusedCol this._focusedRow
needed to be initialized.
